								<div class="title" id="post-title-4045291">
																		Happy Halloween!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205747" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;" >Ihp</a></span> <span class="odate time_1540962337 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Oct 2018 05:05</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4045291">
									

<p>And so ends another stupidly ambitious Halloween series. Did I enjoy working on it as much as the first one? Just about. Is there going to be another Black Autumn? Maybe, but it won't be set in Sloth's Pit&#8212; at least, not exclusively.</p>
<p>I have undying gratitude for <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1540962337" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;">DrChandra</a></span> who let me butcher <a href="/scp-4040">SCP-4040</a> and all elements involved with it. I do wish I'd gotten more crit for this series, but with the Halloween contest going on at the same time, as well as things in my life, I didn't really have time.</p>
<p>This series is dedicated to my cat, Mia, 2006-2018. I hope there's catnip in heaven.</p>
<p>Images are both of my own creation; images of the Pokegama Bay in Superior National Forest<br />
were used as Reference.</p>

							</div>

								
					
